"script": "What if you fell into the deepest spot in the ocean? At first you'd just drift down through warm blue water. But pass a few hundred feet and the light vanishes, leaving you in total darkness. Then the pressure builds, gently at first, then crushing. By the bottom of the Mariana Trench, the weight pressing on you equals fifty jumbo jets stacked on your head. Long before that, your lungs would fold flat and your ribs would cave inward. You wouldn't even reach the seafloor as yourself. You'd arrive as a thin red cloud, swallowed by water seven miles deep.",
